<TITLE> Lt Gen Zahir sent to AFD </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 7 (bdnews24.com)Lt Gen Abu Tayob Mohammad Zahirul Alam, who spent four months at the ministry of foreign affairs for a possible appointment as an ambassador, will now return to the Armed Forces Division, the government announced Tuesday. "The service of army officer Abu Tayob Mohammad Zahirul Alam posted in the ministry of foreign affairs on deputation for appointment as an ambassador has been placed under the Armed Forces Division. The order would come into effect immediately," a ministry of establishment order said. The order did not say anything about his new assignment. Lt Gen Zahirul Alam was transferred from the post of commandant of the National Defence College on June 2 and placed under the foreign ministry for appointment as an ambassador. On the same day, Lt Gen Masud Uddin Chowdhury, then principal staff officer at the Armed Forces Division, was ordered to take up the NDC job. Six days later, Gen Masud was also sent to the foreign ministry. Four months on, the general is now set to fly to Australia for his new role as Bangladesh high commissioner. bd
